events.name: Washington Huskies at Oregon Ducks

headlines.description: Marcus Mariota threw for 198 yards and four touchdowns, including two TD strikes to tight end Colt Lyerla, and No. 2 Oregon beat No. 23 Washington 52-21 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mariota, Lyerla power Oregon by Washington

events.name: Florida State Seminoles at NC State Wolfpack

headlines.description: Mike Glennon found Bryan Underwood for a 2-yard touchdown pass on fourth down with 16 seconds left, helping North Carolina State rally to beat third-ranked Florida State 17-16 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: NC State rallies late, stuns No. 3 FSU

events.name: LSU Tigers at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Mike Gillislee ran for a career-high 146 yards and two touchdowns, bringing No. 10 Florida to life in the second half as the Gators beat fourth-ranked LSU 14-6 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 10 Florida grinds past No. 4 LSU

events.name: Georgia Bulldogs at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Connor Shaw threw two touchdown passes and ran for another, Ace Sanders had a dazzling 70-yard punt return touchdown and No. 6 South Carolina's defense dominated fifth-ranked Georgia in a 35-7 victory Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: S. Carolina slams UGA, stays perfect

events.name: Kansas Jayhawks at Kansas State Wildcats

headlines.description: John Hubert ran for 101 yards and four touchdowns on just 10 carries, Collin Klein had two touchdowns running and throwing and No. 7 Kansas State routed Kansas 56-16 on Saturday.

events.name: West Virginia Mountaineers at Texas Longhorns

headlines.description: Geno Smith passed for four touchdowns, leading No. 8 West Virginia to another wild shootout win in the Big 12, this time taking out No. 11 Texas 48-45 on Saturday night.

events.name: Miami Hurricanes at Notre Dame Fighting Irish

headlines.description: Cierre Wood and George Atkinson III gave Notre Dame its first 100-yard rushing duo in a decade, and Everett Golson came off the bench to lead the No. 9 Irish to a 41-3 victory over Miami on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Golson comes off bench, No. 9 ND rolls

events.name: Nebraska Cornhuskers at Ohio State Buckeyes

headlines.description: Braxton Miller rushed for 186 yards, zig-zagging 72 yards for one score and passing for another, to lead No. 12 Ohio State past No. 21 Nebraska 63-38 on Saturday night before the largest crowd ever at Ohio Stadium.

events.name: Washington State Cougars at Oregon State Beavers

headlines.description: Oregon State survived a shaky start with a 19-6 win over Washington State Saturday.

events.name: Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets at Clemson Tigers

headlines.description: Tajh Boyd threw for a career high 397 yards, and DeAndre Hopkins had 173 yards receiving as No. 15 Clemson beat Georgia Tech 47-31 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 15 Clemson gains 601 yards, dodges GT

events.name: Iowa State Cyclones at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: Jared Barnett threw three touchdowns to Josh Lenz, who later had a scoring toss of his own on a trick play, and Iowa State won 37-23 at No. 15 TCU on Saturday to end the Horned Frogs' FBS-best 12-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Iowa State halts No. 15 TCU's 12-game streak

events.name: Oklahoma Sooners at Texas Tech Red Raiders

headlines.description: Landry Jones passed for two touchdowns, Blake Bell ran for two more and No. 17 Oklahoma beat Texas Tech 41-20, avenging the Sooners' home loss to the Red Raiders last season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Texas Tech's defense succumbs to Oklahoma

events.name: Arizona Wildcats at Stanford Cardinal

headlines.description: Chase Thomas intercepted a tipped pass by Matt Scott in overtime, Stepfan Taylor ran for a 21-yard score two plays later and No. 18 Stanford rallied from a two-touchdown deficit to stun Arizona 54-48 on Saturday.

events.name: Mississippi State Bulldogs at Kentucky Wildcats

headlines.description: Tyler Russell passed for two touchdowns and Mississippi State held Kentucky to just 228 yards on offense, leading the No. 20 Bulldogs to a 27-14 victory Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Russell tosses 2 TDs, leads No. 20 Miss. St.

events.name: Connecticut Huskies at Rutgers Scarlet Knights

headlines.description: Jawan Jamison ran for 110 yards and Wayne Warren returned an interception 25 yards for a touchdown as No. 22 Rutgers suffocated Connecticut 19-3 Saturday to remain undefeated.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jamison runs for 110 as Rutgers rolls UConn

events.name: Northwestern Wildcats at Penn State Nittany Lions

headlines.description: Quarterback Matt McGloin had the go-ahead score with a 5-yard touchdown run with 2:37 left and Penn State rallied from 11 points down in fourth quarter to beat No. 24 Northwestern 39-28 on Saturday.

events.name: UCLA Bruins at California Golden Bears

headlines.description: Zach Maynard matched his career high with four touchdown passes and added a fifth on the ground and California took advantage of six turnovers to stun No. 25 UCLA 43-17 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maynard leads way as Cal stuns sloppy UCLA

events.name: Navy Midshipmen at Air Force Falcons

headlines.description: Right guard Jake Zuzek recovered quarterback Keenan Reynolds' fumbled snap in the end zone and Navy beat Air Force 28-21 in overtime Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fluke TD in overtime lifts Navy past Air Force

events.name: Arkansas Razorbacks at Auburn Tigers

headlines.description: Dennis Johnson rushed for two touchdowns and the Arkansas defense had eight sacks to help the Razorbacks snap a four-game skid with a 24-7 victory over Auburn on Saturday.

events.name: Michigan State Spartans at Indiana Hoosiers

headlines.description: Andrew Maxwell passed for 290 yards and two touchdowns, and Michigan State rallied from a 17-point deficit to defeat Indiana 31-27 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mich. St. erases 17-point deficit, edges Indiana

events.name: Buffalo Bulls at Ohio Bobcats

headlines.description: Ohio 38, Buffalo 31

events.name: South Florida Bulls at Temple Owls

headlines.description: Marcus Green blocked a late field goal attempt and Montel Harris scored two touchdowns to lead Temple to a 37-28 victory over South Florida in a Big East Conference matchup on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Temple trips USF in first game back in Big East

events.name: Boston College Eagles at Army Black Knights

headlines.description: Trent Steelman rushed for 141 yards and scored three times, including a decisive 29-yard touchdown run with 45 seconds left, and Army beat Boston College 34-31 on Saturday to snap an eight-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Army upends BC on Steelman's late rushing TD

events.name: Boise State Broncos at Southern Mississippi Golden Eagles

headlines.description: Joe Southwick threw for three touchdowns and Boise State took advantage of five turnovers to breeze past Southern Mississippi 40-14 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Southwick, Boise State roll past Sothern Miss.

events.name: Virginia Tech Hokies at North Carolina Tar Heels

headlines.description: Gio Bernard rushed for a career-high 262 yards and a touchdown, Sean Tapley and A.J. Blue added two TDs apiece, and North Carolina beat Virginia Tech 48-34 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bernard, North Carolina run past Virginia Tech

events.name: Virginia Cavaliers at Duke Blue Devils

headlines.description: Conner Vernon caught two touchdown passes and set the Atlantic Coast Conference record for career receptions, and Anthony Boone threw four TD passes in his first start, helping Duke crush Virginia 42-17 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Duke's Vernon sets ACC receptions mark in win

events.name: Wake Forest Demon Deacons at Maryland Terrapins

headlines.description: Freshman Stefon Diggs took a short pass 63 yards to set up a 1-yard touchdown run by Justus Pickett with 5:37 left, and Maryland opened the Atlantic Coast Conference portion of its schedule with a 19-14 win over Wake Forest on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maryland rallies by Wake, tops 2011 wins total

events.name: Illinois Fighting Illini at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: Joel Stave threw two touchdown passes and Wisconsin's running game showed signs of life as the Badgers defeated Illinois 31-14 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stave, Wisconsin get back on track in Big Ten

events.name: Michigan Wolverines at Purdue Boilermakers

headlines.description: Denard Robinson rushed for 235 yards and Fitzgerald Toussaint scored twice to help Michigan rout Purdue 44-13 on Saturday afternoon.

events.name: Texas A&M Aggies at Ole Miss Rebels

headlines.description: Johnny Manziel threw for 191 yards and a touchdown and rushed for 129 yards and another score, and Texas A&M rallied from a 10-point fourth-quarter deficit to beat Mississippi 30-27 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Texas A&M rides late rally to win over Ole Miss

events.name: Miami (OH) RedHawks at Cincinnati Bearcats

headlines.description: Camerron Cheatham returned an interception 68 yards for a touchdown, and Cincinnati quarterback Munchie Legaux had a hand in three more touchdowns Saturday night, leading the Bearcats to a 52-14 victory over Miami (Ohio).
headlines.shortLinkText: Legaux accounts for 3 TDs as Cincinnati coasts
